<html>
<head>
<title>ACU Press Release - AX GAS TAX, ACU SAYS</title>
</head>

<body>

For Immediate Release<br>
April 30, 1996<br>
Contact: Jeff Hollingsworth<br>
(703) 836-8602<p>

<center>
<h2>AX GAS TAX, ACU SAYS</h2>
</center>

<p>
 
<P>
ALEXANDRIA, VA.--- "A few months ago, President Clinton admitted that he raised taxes too
much and that it was a mistake. That's all the more reason why he should start making amends
now by supporting the growing movement in Congress to repeal his unnecessary 4.3-cent
gasoline tax. If not, the least he ought to do is make a public commitment not to veto a repeal,"
said American Conservative Union (ACU) Chairman David A. Keene. 
<P>
     "The current increases in gasoline prices stem from many factors," Keene added, "and as
the marketplace deals with them, prices will eventually decrease - - but only to a point. The
marketplace can't make tax burdens disappear. The public has been forced to get along with less
thanks to Clinton's various tax increases. ACU says it's high time government went on a diet,
and a good place to start is by junking the Clinton gas tax."        
<P>
     ACU, founded in 1964, is the country's oldest grassroots conservative lobbying
organization. On behalf of its nearly one million members and supporters, it lobbies Congress on
a wide array of legislative issues.
<P>
                               -30-      

<P>

1007 Cameron Street, Alexandria, VA 22314<br>
PHONE: (703) 836-8602 FAX: (703) 836-8608<br>
