Focus regarding jamming of White House phone lines because of the 
Partial-Birth Abortion Ban Act.  This led to a story in <i>The Washington 
Times</i>, later read by Dr. James Dobson on his daily radio program.
<p>
<b>Jan. 25</b> - Rep. Bob Inglis (R-S.C.) and FRC Director of State and
Local Affairs Larry Huff will speak to the &quot;Caleb Group&quot; in 
Greenville, South Carolina on religion and politics.
<p>
<b>Feb. 2-6</b> - FRC staff will attend the National Religious Broadcasters
Convention in Washington, D.C.
<p></ul>
<li><b>FRC in Print</b>
<p><ul>
