<h2><a name="Facts about"><font size="4">Facts about</font></a><font
size="4"> CHRISTIANdigest Library On-Line</font></h2>

<h3><em>Our Mission Statement:</em> </h3>

<p>CHRISTIANdigest helps brings the message of Jesus Christ to
the world through Christian books and literature. We are
non-denominational.</p>

<h3><em>What does the library consist of?</em></h3>

<p>In most cases, you'll find wholly excerpted chapters from
Christian bestsellers and those that ought to be! Our goal is to
bring you the best writings from the most gifted christian
authors covering a variety of topics including: </p>
<div align="center"><center>

<table border="0">
    <tr>
        <td><ul>
            <li><a href="index.html#Biographies"><b>Biographies</b></a><b>
                </b></li>
            <li><a href="index.html#Christian Living"><b>Christian
                Living</b></a><b> </b></li>
            <li><a href="index.html#Counseling"><b>Counseling</b></a><b>
                </b></li>
            <li><a href="index.html#Issues and Ethics"><b>Issues
                and Ethics</b></a><b> </b></li>
            <li><a href="index.html#Love and Marriage"><b>Love
                and Marriage</b></a><b> </b></li>
        </ul>
        </td>
        <td><ul>
            <li><a href="index.html#Parenting and Family"><b>Parenting
                and Family</b></a><b> </b></li>
            <li><a href="index.html#Prayer and Devotion"><b>Prayer
                and Devotionals</b></a><b> </b></li>
            <li><a href="index.html#Childrens"><b>Childrens </b></a></li>
            <li><a href="index.html#Teens"><b>Teens</b></a><b> </b></li>
            <li><a href="index.html#Fiction"><b>Fiction</b></a></li>
        </ul>
        </td>
    </tr>
</table>
</center></div>

<h3><em>How often do we add books?</em></h3>

<p>All the time! Check back every week or so to see what's new! </p>

<hr size="3" width="70%">

<h2><a name="Welcome to"><font size="4">Welcome to</font></a><font
size="4"> CHRISTIANdigest Library On-Line</font></h2>

<p>Perhaps you have never given much thought to Christian books.
Up until a few years ago, I didn't either. Oh, I knew Christian
bookstores existed, but I thought they only stocked prayer books
and Bibles -- and after all, I still had my old King James
version. </p>

<p>Was I in for a pleasant surprise when I finally wandered in to
the local store in our town one day. It was during a time in my
life that I was trying to sort through some &quot;excess
baggage&quot; --lingering childhood fears that I had carried into
adulthood, guilt over wrongs done to others, etc. I came across
C.S. Lewis' &quot;Mere Christianity&quot; and realized how
undeveloped my faith in Christ really was. I next bought Neil
Anderson's &quot;The Bondage Breaker&quot;, a wonderful insight
into breaking free from negative, self-destructive thoughts and
fears. I followed that with Lloyd Ogilvie's &quot;The Greatest
Counselor in the World&quot; -- a fresh new look at the Holy
Spirit. Wow! I was hooked! Or rather, the Holy Spirit hooked me. </p>

<p>I was also surprised to learn of the variety of topics covered
by Christian books, like: parenting, marriage, business ethics,
counseling, and even fiction. Most importantly, I came across the
NIV (New International Version) bible and for the first time,
Scripture really spoke to me. What a wonderful and exciting
discovery this continues to be. </p>

<p>Many Christian books would routinely make the New York Times
Bestseller List, except they don't report Christian titles. But
the point is well-taken: Christian books are immensely popular
and according to a Gallop study, represent the fastest growing
segment of the book publishing industry. </p>

<p>It's my hope that you will use CHRISTIANdigest often and share
your discoveries with your family, friends and others. And if you
have time, please send us an E-mail <a href="LETTER.HTM">Letter
To The Editor</a>. Your comments and suggestions are very
important to us. Thanks for &quot;logging on&quot;. </p>

<p>Yours in Christ, </p>

<blockquote>
    <p><i>Drew Lawler</i> <br>
    Editor-In-Chief </p>
</blockquote>

<hr size="3" width="70%">

