</DOCHDR>
<html><head><TITLE>Christian Digest Magazine On-Line</title>
<meta name="keywords" content="cristianity, Christ, religion, magazines,
 magazine, family, children, books,"> 
</head>

<body BGCOLOR="#ffffcc" text="000000">

<P>You brought up a very broad subject. You mentioned the lady
at Jabob's well. That is a very good point to show that even
a new Christian, fresh out of the devil's grip, can 
influence others for the sake of Christ. But then on the 
other hand, we read in 1 Tim. 4:16 regarding Pastor Timothy
and his influence over others: "Watch your life and doctrine
closely. Persevere in them, because if you do, you will save
both yourself and your hearers." This shows that a spiritual
leader must be walking upright morally as well as teaching
sound doctrine, not only for his sake, but for the sake of
those whom he will influence. Such influence would extend to
one's salvation as clearly cited. Remember, there will be
no sexually immoral, drunkard, thief, greedy, etc. in the
kingdom of God, but such will be thrown into the lake of
fire (1 Cor. 6:9,10; Gal. 5:19-21; Eph. 5:5-7; Rev. 21:8).

<P>We have many articles at our web site <A HREF="http://www.hhs.net/evangout">http://www.hhs.net/evangout</A> on various subjects, some of
which touch on your initial question.

<P>God bless you.

<P>
