<body bgcolor="#FFFFCC" text="#000000">

<p>Subject: Biblical Contradictions??? </p>

<p>Although there may seem to be contradictions in the Biblical
account, there are really none when carefully examined. If you
will, could you please elaborate on the specific Scriptures which
you believe are contradictions in the creation and flood stories? </p>

<p>Please consider the accounts of Matthew, Mark, Luke and John
They are completely harmonious even though given from the four
different perspectives of these men. For example, when two people
see a crime or an accident and each relate the story, although
the basic facts will be the same, they will each be told in a different
style, with perhaps one pointing out more elaborate facts than
the other and perhaps one leaving out minor details. </p>

<p>You mentioned that you believe in the Lord Jesus. Since he
placed his endorsement on the Word of God (Matthew 5:18; 24:35;
Mark 13:31; Luke 16:17; John 17:17), we can rely on it. </p>

<p>The Bible itself claims to be the Word of God (2 Timothy
3:16,17). </p>

<p>Looking forward to hearing from you. God bless you. </p>

