<p>Subject: set free! </p>

<p>Tell your friend to try the following, which worked for me.
Have him/her take all cigarettes, ash trays and lighters over to
the trash can. Throw the ash trays and lighters out. Break each
cigarette into two or three pieces and throw them all away.
Either as you do this or after you are done, tell Jesus how sorry
you are and how you want to be free of this disgusting, filthy
habit which ruins your personal testimony, not to mention your
lungs. Tell Jesus you want to live for Him and do whatever would
be pleasing and glorifying to Him from today and for the rest of
your life. When you are tempted by the devil to smoke again, cry
out to God to help you overcome, and He will. &quot;No temptation
has seized you except what is common to man. And God is faithful;
he will not let you be tempted beyond what you can bear. But when
you are tempted, he will also provide a way out so that you can
stand up under it&quot; (1 Cor. 10:13). </p>

<p>Whom the Son sets free is free indeed (John 8:36). Hallelujah!
</p>

