<p><strong>Subject: I personally prefer the King James Version</strong></p>

<p>I personally prefer the King James Version of the Bible and do
<br>
not trust any other. I pray before I read the Word that the Holy
Spirit <br>
permits the understanding of God's Word that I don't distort or
misconstrue <br>
its meaning. I am suspicious of the potential harm that one can
obtain from <br>
New International versions, Living or American Bibles. Maybe I
feel they are <br>
diluted or too convenient. If the Bible does not suit our needs
let us modify <br>
the Bible to soothe or satiate our needs under the pretext of
what? allegded <br>
understanding? Let us pray we will all be called to Jesus's
Altar. If I am <br>
wrong! I beg your indulgence and ask forgiveness from God all the
way down to <br>
mortal man. </p>

