</DOCHDR>
<!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC "-//IETF//DTD HTML//EN">
<html>

<head>
<meta http-equiv="Content-Type"
content="text/html; charset=iso-8859-1">
<meta name="keywords"
content="christianity, Christ, religion, magazines,
 magazine, family, children, books,">
<meta name="GENERATOR" content="Microsoft FrontPage 2.0">
<title>QA Forum</title>
</head>

<body bgcolor="#FFFFCC" text="#000000">

<p>Subject: Reconcilliation in Separation <br>
</p>

<p>Prior to my separation from my wife of 28 years some 19 months<br>
ago I had the constant feeling that I was drowning. My health <br>
was deteriorating and I was needing to take more and more <br>
tranquilizers and antidepressants to get through each day. I <br>
was retired from work due to ill health and suffer from <br>
diabetes and a number of different illnesses, however I was <br>
unable to accept my place in the family. I was no longer the <br>
head, or the second in charge, but I came just below the <br>
children. I felt un-loved, my needs were not being met and I <br>
felt desperatly unhappy and a burden to the world.</p>

<p>My ex-wife was loyal to me, as a nurse she understood the <br>
various physical needs that I had, if I was in serious<br>
trouble she would give me assistance as a patient, however I <br>
had no position in our family anymore. She was very involved <br>
in a job which she took very seriously, she was given a car <br>
by her employer, often she needed to travel long distances and<br>
stay away from home over night. Her life was totally full and<br>
there really wasn't any room in it for me.</p>

<p>We attended counselling a number of times before I left,<br>
however I didn't believe that my lot would change while I <br>
lived with her. My ex-wife told me that I would go insane, commit
suicide, be <br>
unable to do voluntry work at our local church and ruin the<br>
lives of our children if left her.</p>

<p>Since leaving my health has improved, I am now working and my<br>
life seems to be coming back together. My relationship with <br>
my kids is improving and I am friends with another lady.<br>
God is still real to me and I believe that he is continuing to <br>
work out his purpose through me.</p>

<p>Peter.</p>

<pre> </pre>

