<body BGCOLOR="#ffffcc" text="000000">

<P>Right before my divorce I found out I was pregnant.  I was devastated 
from the separation my husband had asked for and seeking consolation, had 
begun to see another man.  So I was pregnant and did not know who was the 
father.  I told my ex and he was happy, convinced that we'd make a go of it 
somehow.  Next thing I knew he changed his mind and wanted a divorce.  I went 
ahead with the pregnancy and had a beautiful baby boy.  I am re-married and my 
husbands name is on the birth certificate because we didn't want our son to 
have any bad feelings about who he belonged to.  It felt like the right thing 
to do at the time.  I married a man who was and still is my best friend in the 
whole world.  My question is when my son grows up, should I tell him that my 
husband is not his biological father and that I don't know who that is?  My 
husband doesn't want to because he doesn't want to hurt the child.  
<P>
