<p>Subject: Divorced and pregnant </p>

<p>When Jesus said, &quot;the truth shall set you free&quot; He
wasn't kidding. All of us deserve to know the truth about who we
are and where we come from. I grew up in a home where everything
was told except the truth. My mother died of chronic depression,
my oldest sister committed suicide (after the truth came out
about her daughter conceived in another marriage and adopted),
and my stepsister is an alcoholic. As for me, I hurt, but I face
the truth and speak the truth in love. Truth will not diminish
the pain, love added to the truth helps us walk through it and
grow. </p>

