<html><head><TITLE>Christian Digest Magazine On-Line</title>
<meta name="keywords" content="christianity, Christ, religion, magazines,
 magazine, family, children, books,"> 
</head>

<body BGCOLOR="#ffffcc" text="000000">

<P>A friend of mine was going through a lot of personal and relationship problems 
with her husband (which I was friends with both).  She is a Christian and a mother
of two.  He is not a Christian. The relationship started very 
young (because of a pregnancy) and has been very rocky (a lot of abuse (physcial 
and mental).  In December she became very depressed and after understanding what 
she was going through I helped her move out of her situation. In a way, I was 
helping a friend (the wife), and betraying another (the husband).  The
relationship seemed ended a long time before the seperation and I started a 
relationship with her.  I became very involved with her and her two kids while
she was going through her divorce.  Our relationship became very serious and we
started living with each other and made financial commitments together.  With her
divorce almost finalized, we break up.  Our relationship slowly became more and
more arguing and talk of change, but never a lot happening.  I decided to break
up after she took a weekend to herself and the kids and just stayed away from
home. She knew we had our first counseling appointment on Saturday which we
had been waiting for a long time. It hurt me that she didn't care and didn't want
to go. I really didn't want her to go, but I let anger take control over my
mind and I regret this strongly.  After talking about our relationship, she
told me she felt she never really tried in her marriage (where she tried more
than her spouse) and was going to try to see if he would take her back (He
became involved in another relationship himself that he is living with the girl).
Her big reason for trying again is because he is the father of her children.
She doesn't want to try in our relationship again because she says we started
wrong and the guilt she has from leaving her husband and than getting involved
with me before she was even divorced has kept us from being happy.  <br>
I accept she needs to try to get back together or make sure she has done
everything she could to keep the marriage together, but she doesn't want to give
us a try again.  Just a week before, we were talking about getting engaged after
her divorced and it bothers me she feels this way.  She says if things do not work
out with her marriage (that is still pending final hearing), she will move to her
Sister's in another state.<br>
I really want her to give us another try if things don't work out with her 
marriage.  If a relationship on that level is not possible at the time for us,
I don't want to lose our "best-friend" relationship.  She says I will always be in 
her heart and we'll always be friends, but we both agree if things work out in
her marriage, that wouldn't be possible.  Not sure if their is anything I could do.
<p>
We had something beautiful, but she feels it was wrong in God's eyes and she 
should try getting back with the father of her children who was very abusive
towards her.  I really need to know what other people think about our relationship
and if she is right in her feelings.


Jay

