<body bgcolor="#FFFFCC" text="#000000">

<p>Subject: Saving Marriage</p>

<p>There are several Scriptures in the Bible regarding divorce
and the fact <br>
that God is definately against it. However, I would like to focus
on the mood <br>
swing and depression problems you are having because I can speak
from <br>
experience. <br>
<br>
Have you sought any medical treatment, whether it be from your
family doctor <br>
or a psychiatrist? There is help available for those of us who
suffer from <br>
these problems. I should know because I have received help. God
tells us in <br>
his Word that He will help those who help themselves. You must do
your part <br>
to get better and don't expect God to take care of the problems
by Himself, He <br>
will guide you to the answers. <br>
<br>
For those who have never suffered from depression have a hard
time knowing <br>
what it is like. Try to explain how you feel to your husband.
Maybe even get <br>
some books on the subject. It's not easy and it will take some
time, but I <br>
would hate to see 22years of marriage go down the drain. I wish
you luck and <br>
may God be with you. If you have any questions, please feel free
to email me <br>
(Rick) or my wife Susan.</p>

