<p>Subject: Divorce </p>

<p>I have been married for over 26 years. My wife and I are just
at the pre-separation stage. I do not look at her as a piece of
plastic. She was chosen by God for me, and truly represents the
finest that He could ever offer. I guess that we are having difficulty
appreciating each other's own Love Language, even though I have
begged her to forgive my past mistakes (many, including verbal abuse..)
and stand beside me and go forward. She is a Christian, but seems
unable to forgive despite our efforts at counseling since late
1991, and my efforts to learn of the need to control anger, that anger
is not a sin- just decide what, when, and how much is appropriate-
to do with it. I discovered this internet site today and read the
offering of &quot;The Five Languages of Love&quot;. I just ordered
2 books and hope that serving each other's needs in this way will
work for us and our family. Please pray for us for victory in
Christ! I truly love my wife, un-conditionaly, and want this union
to finally bloom in its Glorious radiance. I hope that you will
be able to reconcile your problem(s) as well, and will offer prayer
as well. </p>

<p>God Bless!! </p>

