<body bgcolor="#FFFFCC" text="#000000">

<p>Subject: Divorce, How to stop it </p>

<p>&nbsp;</p>

<p>John 10:12-15 speaks of the difference between a good shepherd
and a hireling. The hireling &quot;leaveth the sheep and
fleeth&quot; when he &quot;seeth the wolf coming.&quot; Many people
today marry as hirelings. When the wolf comes, they flee. This
curses the earth (spoken of in Malachi) and turns parents' hearts
away from their children and from each other. A Christ-like
marriage involves God. It is not a business arrangement that can
be dissolved when troubles come. In a business arrangement the
parties marry to obtain benefits and will stay only as long as
they're receiving what they bargained for. Christ-like love is
unconditional. It involves a Good Shepherd-type person who will
lay down their life for their spouse. I write this from an
article I recently read. And I write as one who thought about
leaving my husband at one time. Deep in my heart I knew I had not
really ever loved him with an unconditional love. I needed to
sacrifice more time and energy for my husband. </p>

<p>&nbsp;</p>

<hr noshadow>

<p align="center"><font size="2"><b>[</b></font><a
href="../forum.htm"><font size="2"><b>Back to the Forum</b></font></a><font
size="2"><b>]</b></font> </p>

<hr noshadow>
