<body BGCOLOR="#ffffcc" text="000000">

<P>Subject: Marriage
<P>
My wife of 18 years  has "suddenly" stated she no longer loves me and has moved in with another man.  Our marriage has been stormy but loving. In fact until now my love of her has been unshakeable.  The past 2 years have been extreamly difficult. Our teenage son had started to experiment with drugs and had run away. In addition we had to move because of the clousure of the plant were I worked.  Things looked like they were comming together.  Our son was going to return home, seek counseling, and return to school.  <BR>
<BR>

Then my wife went to a high school reunion.  In the space of a weekend her affections were directed to a man who does drugs and has few aspirations and no "worries".  I must add that my wife suffers from depression and has been drinking heavily the last several months.  She has deserted me and her 3 children.  I think it is due to her inability to cope with the chalanges of our son and the conflicts which will arise.  Her previous method of dealing with the children was to let them do whatever they wanted.  The children and I are in therapy now. I love my wife but she is out of control. She has run away from all responsibilty.  I want her to get help and return to her family who loves her. What do we do???<BR>

I pray every day for her and do not know what else to do.
<BR>
<BR>

Thank you. 


<P>
