<body BGCOLOR="#ffffcc" text="000000">

<P>Subject: Children Now Membership Information

<P>Hello,<BR>

 My name is Daniel McGrew. I am having a very serious family problem at this 
time. It involves children, our children, my children. If you can provide any 
help, please let me know. If you cannot provide help, like everyone else, 
please at least send advice or an opinion.<BR>
 Four and a half years ago, DSS (Child Protective Services) in Texas 
discovered something. They discovered that my niece was systematically beating 
her own children with clothes hangers. They found this out because, she sent 
two of her children to the hospitol, she grabbed them by the feet and swung 
them head first into a wall. This very nearly killed them. Thier heads swelled 
up like watermelons, I saw them myself, after she did this to them. DSS 
stepped in and took them away. Finding that the biological mother could not be 
rehabilitated, they searched for someone in the family to adopt the children. 
They found my wife and I we able and willing to adopt them all. There were 
five children at the time. They decided to allow the mother to pick who the 
children went to. The mother was in jail at the time, for this abuse. She 
picked a woman on probation, convicted for her second felony, to take three of 
the children. (DSS had already begun a home-study on my wife and I, and 
stopped it halfway through). She sent two of the other children to woman 
convicted of abandonment of her own six children. Not nice. Last week this 
woman was thrown in jail again for abandonment. The woman who had the three 
children, her health was failing, so she gave them over to me and my wife. 
They are of course brothers and sisters, my great-nieces and nephew. Now DSS 
has taken the two children from the woman convicted of abandonment and put 
them into foster care. I sent my wife to Texas to pick them up. DSS would not 
let her have them, even though we have thier three sisters. They would not 
even let thier three sisters visit them. Stupid. The reason DSS gives for 
this, is they want to rehabilitate the woman convicted of abandonment. So DSS 
wants to keep the brother and sister in foster care until she is 
rehabilitated, for 90 days. In my opinion DSS has no interest in keeping 
families together, they are intentionall keeping this one apart. They are also 
violating a United Nations Convention on children's rights. It says that 
public (government) agencies should strive to keep a family together. I have 
offered them this, and tried to achieve it for this family for over four and 
half years. But, DSS fights me everytime and I can't understand why. They 
wanted someone to adopt the children, my wife and I said that we would be glad 
to. Then they changed thier minds again. What is wrong with Child Protective 
Services in America. They are ruining children left and right, by the 
thousands. They offer children no future security at all. These children have 
been move from person to person, home to home four times over four and half 
years. <BR>

        Now, I cannot imagine why. You think that it might be me. I don't know, you 
tell me. I am a nurse, am in the United States Air Force Reserves, my wife is 
a housewife, she takes real good care of the children that we have, they are 
on the A and B honor roll, we take them to Vacation Bible School, we take the 
to Church, we gave them swimming lessons at the YMCA. What is wrong with Child 
Protective Services in Texas, I think that it may have just a little bit too 
much power and not enough sense to use it wisely, to actually help children. 
Because from what I've seen, it hasn't done anything but make six children 
extremely miserable. There are six now, the last one is not a year old yet, 
and if child protective services has it's way, this is one little girl who may 
never see her brother and sister. Child Protective Services is simply being 
mean and evil. Why would they violate a United Nations Convention on 
Children's Rights. Why can't they make these children happy, they have had 
four years to make these children happy, and they can't do it. Give me and my 
wife a chance, I know that we can. The Lord is with us, I know that we can. <BR>

                        Sincerely,<BR>

                                Daniel L. McGrew
<P>
Steak_Knife@MSN.COM
<P>
Steak knife is because, when I was a little boy I cut my fingers in half with 
a steak knife, while helping my dad clean a table. My fingers are fine now. 
That was over fifteen years ago. 


