<p>Subject: Not in Love with my wife</p>

<p><font face="Times New Roman">I fear that I have committed a
huge sin against my wife and myself.<br>
I fooled myself into thinking that I loved my wife (of 16 months)
and<br>
now I ahave &quot;come clean&quot; with her. She is upset and
about to leave me<br>
for good. The thing is, I *know* I care deeply about her, and
want to live<br>
my life with her. But the litmus test for love is I Corinthians
13, and<br>
those sentiments do not describe how I feel about her.</font></p>

<p><font face="Times New Roman">If we do divorce, this will be
tragic for both of us, but moreso for her since<br>
her love for me is true. She is very depressed about his right
now, and that<br>
is understandable. I don't want her to feel this pain. I have
been praying that<br>
God can change my heart so I can really love her the way she
deserves.<br>
I know I should have considered all of this before we got
married, but that is<br>
water under the bridge now. God does not condone divorce except
for <br>
infedelity, so I just pray that we can salvage this. It will,
however,<br>
take a change inside me.</font></p>

<p><font face="Times New Roman">If there's any advice someone can
give (as well as prayers) I would<br>
greatly appreciate it.<br>
</font></p>



