<p>Subject: not in love with wife </p>

<p>Kevin.....GOOD NEWS!!! Open your Bible and check out 1Cor.13
again. Put in Jesus' name everywhere it says &quot;love&quot;.
You would have to be perfect in order to love your wife according to
all these beautiful examples. This is a love we grow into (as are
all Godly attributes) as we grow in our relationship with the
Lord. Our journey in growing spiritually is not much different
than our physical process. At first we are totally dependant on
our parents, then rolling, crawling, feeding ourselves..... You
get the picture....growing up and learning from our human parents...their
habits, mannerisms...etc. </p>

<p>In these ways we also grow into the likeness of our Heavenly
Father. At times, admittedly, a painfully slow process ... But,
consider the promises of God....He promises to not stop until we
are complete. Cool huh? </p>

<p>Love is a gift from our Lord and the basis of all He has done
for each of us...Your words &quot;I fooled myself into thinking
that I loved my wife&quot; suggests you have much more power than
the Lord you serve. Yet, your statement &quot;I *know* I care
deeply about her&quot; tells me YOU DO LOVE HER. Love is not a
feeling....it is a commitment, a choice to not give up
caring...no matter what...Just as our Lord does for us...(&quot;I
will NEVER leave you nor forsake you....)&quot;Feelings&quot; are
like a summer storm....here and gone....never knowing when the
next clump of clouds will appear and the thunder and lightning
will return......but we know....there will always be another
summer and with it another clump of storm clouds....(at least until
Jesus returns and makes all things new!!!) Yet...can we prove to
anyone that there even was a storm last summer?? One warm day and
a hot wind and the evidence disappears. </p>

<p>Please keep in mind also...The Bible teaches us that we have a
REAL ENEMY...the devil(satan), whose job discription is: to
steal,kill and destroy....any way he can, I might add. He is also
a master of deceit...If you allow him to destroy your marriage...how
is knowing Jesus making any of us any different than the world??? could
it be that the enemy is attacking your marriage because you have the
potential of witnessing through your union? you need to consider
the depth of attack on the family in our culture today in America
as well as all over the world. Adam and Eve were the first
family...and began getting attacked by satan even way back
then...... I know the anguish your wife is experiencing at
hearing that you are not &quot;in love&quot; with her...I also
lived through this experience. It put me in a position to find
out what love is and what love is not. (Remember...the only
reliable source of TRUTH is: THE WORD OF GOD. Definition of Love:
GOD IS LOVE. </p>

<p>My husband and I have a deeper, more loving relationship now
than we did before our crisis...neither of us would have believed
such &quot;oneness&quot; possible...yet we believed our Lord who raises
the dead, makes the blind to see, heals the leper etc.,etc.,etc......could
do the IMPOSSIBLE in our marriage. He did...and we are no different
than you or your wife.(just older probably) He is SO TRUSTWORTHY. Please
do not depend on your feelings. They lie. (and don't forget who
the &quot;father of lies&quot; is....) Jeremiah 29:11 </p>

<p>A sister in the Lord Jo </p>

