<p>Subject: divorce and faith </p>

<p>I would encourage you to ask the Lord to show you
&quot;TRUTH&quot; concerning your &quot;war&quot;. You marriage
has been attacked by our unseen enemy using the things of this world
(remember: the garden of eden story? the enemy deceived the woman by getting
her to question what God meant, then he told her God was lying,
then rewrote Gods' meaning and she believed it!!) Our enemy still uses
the same old line/lies. Getting us to question or rationalize
what we know is the Truth according to God's Word........Our
enemy is still in the business of destroying marriages and families.... The
real question is: Why don't we learn how to stand on God's Truth????
(&quot;we are more than conquerors&quot;)(Greater is He that is
in us, than he that is in the world....) </p>

<p>Please be aware of the unseen war that we, as Christians, are
involved in. It is the enemies job in this war to steal, kill and
destroy our faith, witness, our relationships.... anything that
has the potential to honor to our King. (trying to get us to look
just like the world, so no one will believe Jesus makes us
different) </p>

<p>Our enemy is also described as &quot;the father of
lies&quot;.....and does his job too well. When our marriages are
attacked, we seem only able to see with our eyes, ears, and feelings......
We must learn to ask our King to show us the TRUTH, behind what
we see, hear and feel in our flesh. Please remember: as BELIEVERS
IN OUR LORD AND HIS WORD..... &quot;we are not fighting against
people made of flesh and blood, but against persons without
bodies--the evil rulers of the unseen world, those mighty satanic
beings and great evil princes of darkness who rule this world; and
against huge numbers of wicked spirits in the spirit world.&quot;
Ephesians 6:12 (Living Bible) </p>

<p>Please do not look at the &quot;wind and the waves&quot; the
things that are happening around you....With the help of a few
committed soldiers in the army of God you can learn through this
war to keep your eyes on Jesus and walk on water.... Learn to
stand on the promises of God and His word...Learn the real Truth
about the kind of Love God has for all of us. (and we should have
for others when we allow Jesus to live His life through us) I
Corinthians 13:4-8 (Living Bible) Love is very patient and kind, never
jealous or envious, never boastful or proud, Never haughty or
selfish or rude. Love does not demand its own way. It is not
irritable or touchy. It does not hold grudges and will hardly
even notice when others do it wrong. It is never glad about injustice,
but rejoices whenever TRUTH wins out. If you love someone you
will be loyal to him no matter what the cost. You will always
believe in him, always expect the best of him, and always stand
your ground in defending him. ....Love goes on forever....(Never
gives up) </p>

<p>Be aware...No one can win a war alone. No matter how the
modern movies portray the heroe....Our war in the spiritual realm
is real and we need to learn how to stand back to back as Christian
brothers and sisters...defending each other, protecting each
other, repairing each other (when needed), and at times carrying each other....all
while the war rages around us....keeping our eyes on Jesus (and HIS WORD). </p>

<p>In closing, I will encourage you....NEVER GIVE UP. My marriage
also became a war zone....Because of my love and commitment to
our King,I was not willing to allow the enemy a victory. Our Lord
Jesus is still in the business of raising the dead.(Even
marriages that the enemy has seemed to have killed.) It has been
5 years since our reconciliation and we both continue to praise
the Lord for teaching us the TRUTH about REAL LOVE through the
death and resurrection of our marriage. </p>

<p>A Prayer Warrior in the Kings Service </p>

