<p>Subject: Divorce for the believer</p>

<p>I am looking for guidance in establishing a Christian support
ministry <br>
for believers who find themselves divorced or facing divorce. It
is an <br>
extremely heavy burden to place on a believer that he/she is
condemned as an <br>
adulterer if they wish to remarry after divorce. The fact of the
matter is, we <br>
are all sinners, and to say or think that it is any other way, we
deceive <br>
ourselves, and the truth is not in us! Is any man or woman more
or less sinful <br>
than another? Does God keep score? Is a divorced person who
remarries the only <br>
one faced with being in a state of sin? Did not our Lord say that
merely <br>
looking upon a woman to lust after her is adultery? Who can
escape? No one <br>
except by the grace of God in Jesus Christ. Thanks be to God. </p>

