<p>Subject: responsibility of a spouse being abused<br>
</p>

<p>My marriage was full of arguing and fighting. I was thrown up
against <br>
the wall once, thrown off the bed once, locked in a bathroom and
forgotten, <br>
almost injured with a moving car, forced phusically to pick up
something, and <br>
the grand finale was when I was thrown over his head out into the
yard. I <br>
took a few years to decide to go through with a divorce. I had no
<br>
documentation I was abused. He lied in court about everything.
This man was <br>
supposed to be my loving husband. I divorced him and during the
divorce I met <br>
someone with whom I found the traits I have always wanted in a
husband. I <br>
struggled with the issue of divorce for 15 years, and after we
did counseling <br>
for a few years, and he still kept telling me I was
&quot;crazy&quot;, I should leave, I <br>
hated him and the kids, etc...I decided to go through with a
divorce. <br>
I remarried and have never been more happy in my life. I want to
please God. <br>
I don't think he wants people to be abused and stay in that
situation. I <br>
remarried and hope that God will allow me to finish my life with
some degree <br>
of happiness.<br>
</p>

