<body bgcolor="#FFFFCC" text="#000000">
<p>Parenting/work at home moms</p>
<p>Do you have a job that you can do from home part time? If so, it is a <br>
wonderful alternative to working full time. I currently work for a company <br>
that promotes the &quot;family&quot; and have been blessed with a job as a marketing <br>
writer. I work two full days at the office and leave my son (8 month old) with <br>
a wonderful sitter. Then on the other three days I work from home, I have <br>
another babysitter who comes to my home and watches him while I work in my <br>
home office. I get to &quot;come out for visits&quot; with him, breastfeed, and tip-toe <br>
into his room to watch him sleep. It's a great way to be able to be with your <br>
children AND have a career at the same time! Of course, if I could afford to <br>
quit full time -- my advice to you is DO IT!! Children need their parents more <br>
than ever these days. Good luck to you. And I'd be very interested in knowing <br>
what you decide.</p>
