</DOCHDR>
<html><head><TITLE>Christian Digest Magazine On-Line</title>
<meta name="keywords" content="cristianity, Christ, religion, magazines,
 magazine, family, children, books,"> 
</head>

<body BGCOLOR="#ffffcc" text="000000">

<P>One of the favorite verses of those who hold to the once saved always saved teaching is John 10:28, "I give them eternal life, and they shall never perish; no one can snatch them out of my hand." However, many people neglect to quote verse 27: "My sheep listen to my voice; I know them, and THEY FOLLOW ME." The verb "follow" is continuous-tense in the Greek. No one can snatch any who are continually following Jesus. It is an obviously conditional promise.

<P>There is also an obvious condition to the very heart of Paul's gospel message. 1 Cor. 15:2 states: "By this gospel you are saved, IF YOU hold firmly to the word I preached to you. OTHERWISE, YOU HAVE BELIEVED IN VAIN." Why is it that most of the eternal security people skip over this verse when quoting Paul's gospel of Christ's death, burial and resurrection? The answer is obvious.

<P>The writer of Hebrews told the Christians: "We have come to share in Christ IF WE HOLD firmly TILL THE END the confidence we had at first" (Heb. 3:14). It doesn't say that God will unconditionally hold us firmly till the end.

<P>Lastly, God Himself, who knows all there is to know about His own grace and keeping power, spoke these words from His throne after the finished work of Christ was completed on the cross: "But the cowardly, the unbelieving, the vile, the murderers, the sexually immoral, those who practice magic arts, the idolaters
and all liars--their place will be in the fiery lake of
burning sulfur. This is the second death" (Rev. 21:8).
Notice there is no fine print which reads, "unless they
were ever saved." There is no difference between a
sexually immoral person who was never saved and a saved
person who later becomes sexually immoral and dies in
an unrepentant state (1 Cor. 6:9,10; Eph. 5:5-7; Gal.
5:19-21). Notice also that the "unbelieving" are not
the only ones who go to the lake of fire, as the
Calvinists teach. Furthermore, the once saved always
saved teaching is a "license for immorality" (Jude 4),
since it teaches that if you were ever saved and then
become sexually immoral, you will still go to Heaven
even if you do not repent. If this isn't a license for
immorality, then a license for immorality does not
exist.

<P>For more information, visit our web site at <A HREF="http://www.hhs.net/evangout">http://www.hhs.net/evangout</A>.

<P>God bless you.

<P>
