<p>Subject: Eternal Security</p>

<p>The reason I believe in eternal security is because Jesus told
me in His Word that when the Holy Spirit comes to dwell in me
that He will never leave me till I go to the Father. That to me
is eternal security. Besides if you think that becoming sexually
impure is a way to loose your salvation then why did Jesus have
to come and die on the Cross. You seem to believe that you are
the one that can hold your salvation and this is so untrue of
what the Bible as a whole teaches. Sure you can take scripture
out of context and seem to prove a point but in my heart there is
nothing that csn change the fact that Jesus lives there and is
there until He returns to take me home to Him. If we could save
ourselves by staying away from sin then Jesus would not have had
to go to the Cross too cover that sin with His precious sin. As
for a license too sin, if Jesus lives in your heart you have a
conviction of that sin when you committ it and confession is the
next response, I know I still sin everyday. Is lying, stealing,
gossipping,etc.,etc., any less sin in God's eyes' than sexually
immmorality? </p>

